So with any form of transaction, there's often a desire to collect or apply a fee, similar to a small service charge every time you transfer money at a bank, or the way royalties or taxis are collected for particular transfers. The original Token program has no mechanism for this. The workaround was the freezer users account and forced them to go through a third party. With Token 22, you can actually configure a transfer fee directly on a mint, enabling fees to be collected at the protocol level. So every time you transact with a given mint, the specific fee is set aside in the recipient account. This fee is actually untouchable by the recipient and can only be accessed by the withdrawal authority. So this guide walks you through how to use the transfer fee mint extension to add a transfer feed to a mint, and how to access all of the withheld fees. So, let's take a look.
